.\" CPUTIL(1)                                                              CPUTIL(1)
.\" Manpage for CPUTIL
.TH CPUTIL 1  "version X.X" "USER COMMANDS"

.SH NAME
.B cputil
- Configurator Tumar CSP command line tool

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./cputil 
.RB [ OPERATION ]
.RB [ OPTIONS ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cputil 
is a command line tool for control the settings of key information, work with key information and data, located in a key container from the shell.

It can be used for:
.RS
.nf
inf  - Get information about the version of CSP, key algorithms, profiles, etc.
key  - Use operations with the key information: create / delete profile, generation / removal key
req  - Use operations with the PKIX requests
imp  - Use operations with import keys and certificates to key container
exp  - Use operations with export keys and certificates from key container
cmp  - Work with CA by Certificate Management Protocol
ocsp - Work with Online Certificate Status Protocol Server
.RE

The cputil program provides a rich variety of commands (command in the SYNOPSIS above), each of which often has a wealth of options and arguments.
When selecting an option will be displayed additional features on its.
.YS

//--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

.SH NAME OPERATION
.TP
.B inf

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./cputil inf [-v] [-a] [-p]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Information of version, profiles etc. Can be used to get information about the version of CSP, key algorithms, profiles, etc.

.SH OPTIONS
.IP "-v, --version"
Displays information about the version of OS, utility, CSP, developer, library, licence

.IP "-a, --algorithms"
Displays information about all supported algorithms

.IP "-p, --profiles"
Displays information about all existing profiles list in configuration file /TumarCSP/etc/cptumar.conf
.YS

//--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

.SH NAME OPERATION
.TP
.B key

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./cputil key [-p <profile>] [-l] [-c <path>] [-x <password>] [-d] [-z] [-s <SN>] [-g <OID>]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Keys operations. Can be used to work with the key information: create / delete profile, generation / removal key

.SH OPTIONS
.PP 
Required:
.IP "-p, --profile name"
This option is required. Specifies the name of the profile used.

.IP "-p, --profile name"
This option is required. Specifies the name of the profile used.

.PP
Choice:
.IP "-l, --list of keys"
Display information by profile

.IP "-c <path>, --create profile"
Create a profile with the following characteristics

.IP "-x <password>,	--containers password"
Set password to key container when creating a profile (optional)

.IP "-d, --delete profile"
Use with OPTION -p and/or -x only		

.IP "-z, --delete container"
associated with this profile

.IP "-s <SN>, --delete key"
from container by serial number (first few characters, "all"-delete all keys)

.IP "-g <oid>, -- generation of key(-s)"
To generate the keys use either a pre-sentence (sign, exch, auth) or indicate a specific OID
.RS
.nf
sign - EC 256/512 (GOST 34.310-2004 A)
exch - EC 256/512 (GOST 34.310-2004 A/Xch)
auth - RSA 2048
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.BI ./cputilkey	-p	Test_profile	-c	/TumarCSP/keys/TEST_CONTAINER.bin
.TP
.PP
create a profile with the following characteristics
.RS
.nf
a) directiory - /TumarCSP/keys (If the specified directory does not exist, it will be created automatically)
b) key container name - TEST_CONTAINER.bin
c) profile name - Test_profile
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: in the configuration file /TumarCSP/etc/cptumar.conf will be created corresponding profile

.TP
.BI ./cputil	key	-p	Test_profile	-c	/TumarCSP/keys/TEST_CONTAINER.bin	-x	12345
.TP
.PP
create a profile with the following characteristics
.RS
.nf
a) directiory - /TumarCSP/keys
b) key container name - TEST_CONTAINER.bin
c) profile name - Test_profile
e) password for container - 12345
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: in the configuration file /TumarCSP/etc/cptumar.conf will be created corresponding profile			

.TP
.BI ./cputil	key	-l	-p	Test_profile
.TP
.PP
display information by profile with the following characteristics
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: on display will provide information of keys by specified profile

.TP
.BI ./cputil	key	-g	sign	-p	Test_profile
.TP
.PP
create a key container and the generation of key information with the following characteristics
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) key sign - EC 256/512 (GOST 34.310-2004 A)  
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: the key will be generated by the specified profile 
.PP
NOTE: if you need to generate key by specifying OID use -g <OID> (example: ./cputil key -g 1.3.6.1.4.1.6801.1.8.23 -p Test_profile)

.TP
.BI ./cputil	key	-p	Test_profile	-d
.TP
.PP
delete profile with the following characteristics
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: the profile will be deleted

.TP
.BI ./cputil	key	-p	Test_profile	-d	-z
.TP
.PP
delete profile and key container
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: the profile and key container will be deleted

.TP
.BI ./cputil	key	-p	Test_profile	-s	e8ef
.TP
.PP
delete key with SN e8ef3f966b069d4318ed51018cebbe65049c9a6d240e753e32abda959b841031
result: key will be deleted

.TP
.BI ./cputil	key	-p	Test_profile	-s	all
.TP
.PP
delete all keys without deleting the profile
result: all keys will be deleted
.YS

//--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

.SH NAME OPERATION
.TP
.B req

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./cputil req [-p <profile>] [-s <SN>] [-o <path>] [-u <URL>] [-z <URL>] [-f <format>] [-m <DName>] [-t <type>]

.SH DESCRIPTION
- Create PKIX requests. Can be used to work with PKIX requests

.SH OPTIONS
.PP 
Required:
.IP "-p, --profile name"
This option is required. Specifies the name of the profile used.

.IP "-s <SN>, --serial number"
Key serial number (first few characters)

.IP "-o <path>,	--output file name"
Specify the path to the file for export request-file
.PP
OR/AND:
.IP "-u <URL> --Remote CA server URL"
.IP "-z <URL> --Proxy server URL"
scheme: http(s)/socks4/socks5. Optional.

.PP
Optional:
.IP "-f <format>, --Output format"
der|pem, default: der

.IP "-m <DName>, --Template DName"
default: empty

.IP "-t <type>, --Output type"
pkcs10|pkcs7, default: pkcs10

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.BI ./cputil	req	-p	Test_profile	-s	2a07	-o	/TumarCSP/req
.TP
.PP
create pkcs10 certificate request with the following characteristics (If you want to use pem, specify -f pem)
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - 2a07
c) request file name - /TumarCSP/req
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: pkcs10 certificate request will be saved into the file /TumarCSP/req.p10

.TP
.BI ./cputil	req	-p	Test_profile	-s	2a07	-o	/TumarCSP/req	-t	pkcs7
.TP
.PP
create pkcs7 certificate request with the following characteristics (If you want to use pem, specify -f pem)
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - 2a07
c) request file name - /TumarCSP/req
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: pkcs7 certificate request will be saved into the file /TumarCSP/req.p7r	

.TP
.BI ./cputil	req	-p	test	-s	ae4592520561d2efd40d2f2a916cfe765e6aeff47678dca7fe1b55f7a3e2fc56	-o	result.bin	-u	http://172.16.172.221:62310	-m	"CN=GOST_RAUTIL_USER_1Y;O=Template;C=KZ"
.TP
.PP
create pkcs10 request for a new key and send it to the CA (specify also the key generation template and RA service URL). The container must contain key and certificate (DN name in PKCS#10 will be extracted from existing certificates)
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - test
b) serial number - ae4592520561d2efd40d2f2a916cfe765e6aeff47678dca7fe1b55f7a3e2fc56
c) request file name - result.bin
d) remote CA server URL - http://172.16.172.221:62310
e) template DName - CN=GOST_RAUTIL_USER_1Y;O=Template;C=KZ
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: pkcs10 certificate request will be saved into the file result.bin and will be send to the CA URL - http://172.16.172.221:62310

.TP
.BI ./cputil	req	-p	test	-s	52574031c6849bd1f3f3eaf7550e7fbdca8ad5c3100877cce9c657c875327353	-t	pkcs7	-o	result.bin	-u	http://172.16.172.221:62310	-m	"CN=GOST_RAUTIL_USER_1Y;O=Template;C=KZ"
.TP
.PP
create pkcs7 request for a new key and send it to the CA (specify also the key generation template and RA service URL). The container must contain key and certificate to sign the PKCS#10 request.
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - test
b) serial number - 52574031c6849bd1f3f3eaf7550e7fbdca8ad5c3100877cce9c657c875327353
c) output type - pkcs7
d) request file name - result.bin
e) remote CA server URL - http://172.16.172.221:62310
e) template DName - GOST_RAUTIL_USER_1Y;O=Template;C=KZ
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: pkcs7 certificate request will be saved into the file result.bin and will be send to the CA URL - http://172.16.172.221:62310	
.YS

//--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

.SH NAME OPERATION
.TP
.B imp

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./cputil imp [-p <profile>] [-c <path>] [-a <path>] [-k <path>] [-x <password>]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Import information to container. Can be used to work with import keys and certificates operations

.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Required:
.IP "-p, --profile name"
This option is required. Specifies the name of the profile used.

.PP
Choise:
.IP "-c <path>, --import certificate from file"
Specify the path to the certificate-file for import

.IP "-a <path>, --import CA certificate from file"
Specify the path to the CA-certificate-file for import

.IP "-k <path>, --import key from file"
Specify the path to the key-file for import

.IP "-x <password>,	--password for key file"
Optional, otherwise console input				

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.BI ./cputil	imp	-p	Test_profile	-k	/TumarCSP/bin/test_keys/key1.p8	-x1
.TP
.PP
import key to key container with the following characteristics
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) key file name - /TumarCSP/bin/test_keys/key1.p8
c) password for key file - 1
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: key will be imported into the key container

.TP
.BI ./cputil	imp	-p	Test_profile	-c	/TumarCSP/bin/test_keys/cert1.cer
.TP
.PP
import certificate to key container with the following characteristics (before importing the certificate in the key container must be a corresponding key)
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) certificate file name - /TumarCSP/bin/test_keys/cert1.cer
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: certificate will be imported into the key container

.TP
.BI ./cputil	imp	-p	Test_profile	-a	/TumarCSP/bin/test_keys/ca.cer
.TP
.PP
import CA certificate to key container with the following characteristics (before importing the CA certificate in the key container must be a corresponding key)
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) CA certificate file name - /TumarCSP/bin/test_keys/ca.cer
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: CA certificate will be imported into the key container
.YS

//--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

.SH NAME OPERATION
.TP
.B exp

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./cputil exp [-p <profile>] [-s <SN>] [-c <path>] [-a <path>] [-h <path>] [-k <path>] [-v <path>] [-x <password>] [-f <format>]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Export information from container. Can be used to work with export keys and certificates operations

.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Required:
.IP "-p, --profile name"
This option is required. Specifies the name of the profile used

.IP "-s <SN>, --serial number"
Key serial number (first few characters)

.PP
Choice:
.IP "-c <path>, --export certificate to file"
Specify the path to the file for export certificate

.IP "-a <path>, --export CA certificate to file"
Specify the path to the file for export CA certificate

.IP "-h <path>, --export certificate chain (PKCS7)"
Specify the path to the file for export certificate chain

.IP "-k <path>, --export Pkcs#8 key to file"
Specify the path to the file for export Pkcs#8 key

.IP "-v <path>, --export Pkcs#12 key to file"
Specify the path to the file for export Pkcs#12 key

.PP
Optional:
.IP "-x <password>, --password for key file" 
Optional, otherwise console input		

.IP "-f <format>, --output format der|pem, default: der"

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.BI ./cputil	exp	-p	Test_profile	-s	2a07	-c	/TumarCSP/cert_exp.cer
.TP
.PP
export certificate from key container with the following characteristics (If you want to use pem, specify -f pem)
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - 2a07
c) certificate export file name - /TumarCSP/cert_exp
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: certificate will be exported into the file

.TP
.BI ./cputil	exp	-p	Test_profile	-s	2a07	-a	/TumarCSP/ca_cert_exp.cer
.TP
.PP
export CA certificate from key container with the following characteristics (If you want to use pem, specify -f pem)
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - 2a07
c) CA certificate export file name - /TumarCSP/ca_cert_exp
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: CA certificate will be exported into the file

.TP
.BI ./cputil	exp	-p	Test_profile	-s	2a07	-h	/TumarCSP/chain_cert_exp
.TP
.PP
export certificate chain from key container with the following characteristics (If you want to use pem, specify -f pem)
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - 2a07
c) Certificate chain export file name - /TumarCSP/chain_cert_exp
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: Certificate chain will be exported into the file /TumarCSP/chain_cert_exp.p7b

.TP
.BI ./cputil	exp	-p	Test_profile	-s	2a07	-k	/TumarCSP/key_exp8	-x1
.TP
.PP
export key (Pkcs#8) from key container with the following characteristics (If you want to use pem, specify -f pem)
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - 2a07
c) password for export key file - 1
d) key export file name - /TumarCSP/key_exp8
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: key will be exported into the file /TumarCSP/key_exp8.p8

.TP
.BI ./cputil	exp	-p	Test_profile	-s	2a07	-v	/TumarCSP/key_exp12	-x1
.TP
.PP
export key (Pkcs#12) from key container with the following characteristics (If you want to use pem, specify -f pem)
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - 2a07
c) password for export key file - 1
d) key export file name - /TumarCSP/key_exp12
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: key will be exported into the file /TumarCSP/key_exp12.pfx
.YS

//--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

.SH NAME OPERATION
.TP
.B cmp

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./cputil cmp [-t <type>] [-p <profile>] [-s <SN>] [-u <URL>] [-z <URL>] [-i <path>] [-o <path>] [-d <OID>] [-x <secret>] [-a <transID>] [-v <date>] [-r <status>] 

.SH DESCRIPTION
Certificate Management Protocol. Can be used to work with CA by Certificate Management Protocol

.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Required:
.IP "-t <type>,	--request type ir|cr|rr|kur"
.RS
.nf
ir  - Initialization Request
cr  - Certification Request
kur - Key Update Request
rr  - Revocation Request
.RE

.IP "-p, --profile name"
This option is required. Specifies the name of the profile used.

.IP "-s <SN>, --serial number"
Key serial number (first few characters).

.IP "-u <URL>, --remote CMP server URL"
URL must be in the format <protocol>://<host>:port.

.IP "-z <URL>, --proxy server URL"
scheme: http(s)/socks4/socks5. Optional."

.IP "-i <path>, --output request file. Optional."

.IP "-o <path>, --output response file. Optional."

.IP "-d <ID>, --userID for IR request"

.IP "-x <secret>, --secret for IR request"
Optional, otherwise console input

.IP "-a <transID>, --transaction ID for polling requests"

.IP "-v <date>, --new date validity for KUR request (YYYYMMDDHHMMSS)"

.IP "-r <status>"
Status for rr request:
.RS
.nf
1  - keyCompromise
6  - certificateHold
8  - removeFromCRL
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.BI ./cputil	cmp	-t	ir	-p	Test_profile	-s	64a7	-u	"http://192.168.7.203:62295"	-i	req.txt	-o	resp.txt	-d	test	-x	1234567890
.TP
.PP
create the initialization request (needs to be pre-generated key by specified profile) with the following characteristics 
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - 64a7
c) CMP url - http://192.168.7.203:62295
d) ID - test
e) Secret - 1234567890
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: the initialization request will be sent to the server (request will be assigned to a transaction, on display will be showed the processing status)

.TP
.BI ./cputil	cmp	-t	ir	-p	Test_profile	-s	64a7	-u	"http://192.168.7.203:62295"	-i	req.txt	-o	resp.txt	-d	test	-x	1234567890	-a	JH0M48C5JJ97DF9Z
.TP
.PP
order to check the status of processing the request you must specify a transaction ID and sent request to server again
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - 64a7
c) CMP url - http://192.168.7.203:62295
d) ID - test
e) Secret - 1234567890
f) Transaction ID - JH0M48C5JJ97DF9Z
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: server returns a status of transaction processing or the certificate which automatically install into the key container by specified profile

.TP
.BI ./cputil	cmp	-t	cr	-p	Test_profile	-s	f6b8	-u	"http://192.168.7.203:62295"	-i	req.txt	-o	resp.txt	-d	test	-x	1234567890
.TP
.PP
create the certificate request (needs to be pre-generated key by specified profile) with the following characteristics
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - f6b8
c) CMP url - http://192.168.7.203:62295
d) ID - test
e) Secret - 1234567890
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: the certificate request will be sent to the server (request will be assigned to a transaction, on display will be showed the processing status)			

.TP
.BI ./cputil	cmp	-t	kur	-p	Test_profile	-s	f6b8	-u	"tcp://192.168.7.203:62295"	-i	req.txt	-o	resp.txt	-d	test	-x	1234567890	-v	20130404140000
.TP
.PP
create the certificate change request with the following characteristics 
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - f6b8
c) CMP url - http://192.168.7.203:62295
d) ID - test
e) Secret - 1234567890
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: the certificate request will be sent to the server, request will be processed and the certificate will be issued a certificate store				

.TP
.BI ./cputil	cmp	-t	rr	-p	Test_profile	-s	f6b8	-u	"tcp://192.168.7.203:62295"	-i	req.txt	-o	resp.txt	-d	test	-x	1234567890	-r	1
.TP
.PP
create the certificate revoke request with the following characteristics 
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - f6b8
c) CMP url - http://192.168.7.203:62295
d) ID - test
e) Secret - 1234567890
f) Revoke by compromise
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: the certificate revoke request will be sent to the server, request will be processed and the certificate will be revoke and ceftificate information added to CRL
.YS

//--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

.SH NAME OPERATION
.TP
.B ocsp

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./cputil ocsp [-p <profile>] [-s <SN>] [-u <URL>] [-z <URL>] [-i <path>] [-o <path>]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Online Certificate Status Protocol. Can be used to work with Online Certificate Status Protocol Server

.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Required:
.IP "-p, --profile name"
This option is required. Specifies the name of the profile used.

.IP "	
-s <SN>, --serial number"
Key serial number (first few characters).

.IP "
-u <URL>, --remote CMP server URL"
URL must be in the format <protocol>://<host>:port.

.IP "-z <URL> Proxy server URL"
scheme: http(s)/socks4/socks5. Optional.

.IP "-i <path> Output request  file. Optional."

.IP "-o <path> Output response file. Optional."

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.BI ./cputil	ocsp	-p	Test_profile	-s	64a7	-u	"tcp://192.168.7.203:62201"
.TP
.PP
create the ocsp request for certificate validation
.RS
.nf
a) profile name - Test_profile
b) first few characters in key serial number - 64a7
c) CMP url - http://192.168.7.203:62201
.RE
.TP
.PP
result: the ocsp request will be sent to the server (on display will be showed the certificate status)				

